{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01NfAa4ULwZkkQ1x8EnuTdg9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n- **app-producer** is `1/1 Running` (Ready).\n- **`/app` vhost** has `app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages accumulating (6 and growing, since the producer publishes on a loop).\n- **Cluster** shows all 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running and healthy.\n\nRoot cause: `app-user`'s permissions on the `/app` vhost had an empty `configure` regex, so it was denied when trying to declare (`PUT`) `app-queue`, causing the producer to crash-loop with `not_authorised`. Fix was a single `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"^app-queue$\" \".*\" \".*\"` — scoped narrowly to just `app-queue` rather than granting broad configure rights, no CRDs/operators used, no data touched (no data loss risk)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":733,"cache_read_input_tokens":46629,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":733},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b3e07e9-ae89-4dde-a658-52dccc402d3b","uuid":"a47dae2e-7b48-4d2d-bee9-77a1f7b09399","request_id":"req_011CcaqC5ohjrbePQ1YYZRH2"}
